<div class="markdown prose w-full break-words dark:prose-invert dark"><h3><strong>Difference Between Signal and Busy Waiting</strong></h3><p>A <strong>signal</strong> (in OS or concurrency) and <strong>busy waiting</strong> are both ways to handle waiting, but they work in very different ways.</p><table><thead><tr><th>Feature</th><th><strong>Signal</strong></th><th><strong>Busy Waiting</strong></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>CPU Usage</strong></td><td><strong>Does not use CPU</strong> while waiting</td><td><strong>Consumes CPU continuously</strong></td></tr><tr><td><strong>Mechanism</strong></td><td>Uses <strong>interrupts, event queues, or condition variables</strong></td><td>Uses a <strong>loop checking a condition repeatedly</strong></td></tr><tr><td><strong>Efficiency</strong></td><td>Highly efficient</td><td>Inefficient (wastes CPU cycles)</td></tr><tr><td><strong>OS Involvement</strong></td><td>OS <strong>blocks and wakes up</strong> processes when needed</td><td>No OS involvement; the process spins continuously</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Common Use Cases</strong></td><td>Synchronization between threads, I/O completion, mutex waiting</td><td>Polling for data availability, spinlocks (only for short waits)</td></tr></tbody></table><hr><h2><strong>1. What is a Signal? (Blocking Mechanism)</strong></h2><p>A <strong>signal</strong> is a mechanism where a thread/process <strong>sleeps until an event occurs</strong> and is woken up by another thread, the OS, or a hardware interrupt.</p><h3><strong>How It Works:</strong></h3><ol><li>The waiting thread <strong>suspends execution</strong> (goes into a blocked state).</li><li>Another process or the OS <strong>sends a signal</strong> (e.g., via a <code>condition_variable</code> or <code>futex</code>).</li><li>The thread <strong>wakes up and resumes execution</strong>.</li></ol><h3><strong>Example in C (Using Condition Variables)</strong></h3><pre class="!overflow-visible"><div class="contain-inline-size rounded-md border-[0.5px] border-token-border-medium relative bg-token-sidebar-surface-primary dark:bg-gray-950"><div class="flex items-center text-token-text-secondary px-4 py-2 text-xs font-sans justify-between rounded-t-md h-9 bg-token-sidebar-surface-primary dark:bg-token-main-surface-secondary select-none">c</div><div class="sticky top-9 md:top-[5.75rem]"><div class="absolute bottom-0 right-2 flex h-9 items-center"><div class="flex items-center rounded bg-token-sidebar-surface-primary px-2 font-sans text-xs text-token-text-secondary dark:bg-token-main-surface-secondary"><span class="" data-state="closed"><button class="flex gap-1 items-center select-none px-4 py-1" aria-label="Copy"><svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="icon-xs"><path fill-rule="evenodd" clip-rule="evenodd" d="M7 5C7 3.34315 8.34315 2 10 2H19C20.6569 2 22 3.34315 22 5V14C22 15.6569 20.6569 17 19 17H17V19C17 20.6569 15.6569 22 14 22H5C3.34315 22 2 20.6569 2 19V10C2 8.34315 3.34315 7 5 7H7V5ZM9 7H14C15.6569 7 17 8.34315 17 10V15H19C19.5523 15 20 14.5523 20 14V5C20 4.44772 19.5523 4 19 4H10C9.44772 4 9 4.44772 9 5V7ZM5 9C4.44772 9 4 9.44772 4 10V19C4 19.5523 4.44772 20 5 20H14C14.5523 20 15 19.5523 15 19V10C15 9.44772 14.5523 9 14 9H5Z" fill="currentColor"></path></svg>Copy</button></span><span class="" data-state="closed"><button class="flex select-none items-center gap-1"><svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="icon-xs"><path d="M2.5 5.5C4.3 5.2 5.2 4 5.5 2.5C5.8 4 6.7 5.2 8.5 5.5C6.7 5.8 5.8 7 5.5 8.5C5.2 7 4.3 5.8 2.5 5.5Z" fill="currentColor" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"></path><path d="M5.66282 16.5231L5.18413 19.3952C5.12203 19.7678 5.09098 19.9541 5.14876 20.0888C5.19933 20.2067 5.29328 20.3007 5.41118 20.3512C5.54589 20.409 5.73218 20.378 6.10476 20.3159L8.97693 19.8372C9.72813 19.712 10.1037 19.6494 10.4542 19.521C10.7652 19.407 11.060